solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)

solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.Id JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T4 ON T1.Maker  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.weight  <  3500 AND T4.FullName != 'Ford Motor Company';
answer: SELECT T1.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId INNER JOIN model_list AS T3 ON T2.Model = T3.Model WHERE T1.Weight < 3500 AND T2.Make != 'Ford Motor Company'

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.Id JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T4 ON T1.Maker  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.weight  <  3500 AND T4.FullName != 'Ford Motor Company';

solution: SELECT CountryName FROM countries EXCEPT SELECT T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.countryId  =  T2.Country;
answer: SELECT T2.CountryName FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN countries AS T2 ON T1.Country = T2.CountryId GROUP BY T2.CountryName HAVING COUNT(T1.Id) = 0

solution: select t1.id ,  t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id  =  t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*)  >=  2 intersect select t1.id ,  t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id  =  t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model  =  t3.model group by t1.id having count(*)  >  3;
answer: SELECT T1.Maker, T1.Id FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Maker HAVING COUNT(T1.Id) > 3 AND COUNT(DISTINCT T2.Model) >= 2

solution: SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >  3;
answer: SELECT T1.Id, T1.Maker FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING COUNT(T2.Model) >= 2 AND SUM(CASE WHEN T1.Country = '2' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 3

solution: SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country GROUP BY T1.countryId HAVING count(*)  >  3 UNION SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T3 ON T2.Id  =  T3.Maker WHERE T3.Model  =  'fiat';
answer: SELECT T1.Id, T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 INNER JOIN car_makers AS T2 ON T1.CountryId = T2.Country WHERE (T2.Maker IN ( SELECT Maker FROM model_list GROUP BY Maker HAVING COUNT(Model) > 3 ) OR T2.Maker = 1 AND Model = 'fiat')

solution: select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*)  >  3 union select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id  =  t3.maker where t3.model  =  'fiat';
answer: SELECT T1.CountryId, T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 INNER JOIN car_makers AS T2 ON T1.CountryId = T2.Country WHERE T2.Id IN ( SELECT T3.Maker FROM model_list AS T3 GROUP BY T3.Maker HAVING COUNT(T3.Model) > 3 )

solution: SELECT count(*) ,  District FROM city WHERE Population  >  (SELECT avg(Population) FROM city) GROUP BY District
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.District) ,  SUM(T2.Population) FROM city AS T1 INNER JOIN ( SELECT District ,  AVG(Population) FROM city GROUP BY District ) AS T2 ON T1.District = T2.District WHERE T2.Population > T1.Population

solution: SELECT count(*) ,  District FROM city WHERE Population  >  (SELECT avg(Population) FROM city) GROUP BY District
answer: SELECT District, COUNT(CASE WHEN Population > ( SELECT AVG(Population) FROM city ) THEN 1 END) AS above_average FROM city GROUP BY District

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
answer: SELECT T2.Continent, AVG(T2.LifeExpectancy) AS AverageLifeExpectancy, SUM(T2.Population) FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.Code WHERE T2.LifeExpectancy < 72 GROUP BY T2.Continent

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
